attachments.title: The Rise and Fall of Bitcoin Billionaire Arthur Hayes
attachments.text: The BitMEX cofounder created a cryptocurrency exchange that has traded trillions. Now he’s wanted by U.S. authorities, and insiders wonder whether he and his partners are villains—or victims of a two-tiered justice system that favors big banks over brash outsiders.

text: Interesting : "Prosecutors allege that Hayes and his business partners violated the Bank Secrecy Act by failing to implement and maintain an adequate anti-money-laundering program—to weed out bad actors and dirty money." The hypocrisy of the system makes me absolutely sick when you compare this with this situation.   <https://www.reuters.com/article/us-hsbc-probe-idUSBRE8BA05M20121211>

attachments.title: HSBC to pay $1.9 billion U.S. fine in money-laundering case
attachments.text: HSBC Holdings Plc agreed to pay a record $1.92 billion in fines to U.S. authorities for allowing itself to be used to launder a river of drug money flowing out of Mexico and other banking lapses.
